  "local_port": 48650,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get free singing lessons via Skype?",
  "response": "Finding free singing lessons via Skype can be challenging, as most professional instructors charge for their services. However, there are a few options you can explore:\n\n1. **Online Platforms and Forums:**\n   - **Reddit:** Websites like r/singing and r/musiclessons often have users who might offer free lessons or advice. You can post asking if anyone is willing to give free lessons over Skype.\n   - **Quora:** Similar to Reddit, you can ask for free lesson offers on Quora.\n\n2. **Social Media:**\n   - **YouTube:** Some YouTube channels offer free vocal lessons and tips. While not personalized via Skype, you can learn a lot from these resources.\n   - **Instagram/Facebook Groups:** Join singing and music-related groups where you can connect with others who might offer free lessons.\n\n3. **Volunteering and Non-Profit Organizations:**\n   - Some community centers or non-profit arts organizations might offer free or low-cost lessons. They may use platforms like Skype, especially in the current remote environment.\n\n4. **Student Teachers:**\n   - Music students often need to practice teaching. They might offer free lessons to gain experience. You can find them by contacting local music schools or colleges with music programs.\n\n5. **Bartering Services:**\n   - If you have a skill or service to offer, you might find someone willing to exchange singing lessons for your service via platforms like Craigslist or local classifieds.\n\n6. **Free Trials:**\n   - Some instructors offer a free trial lesson. While not ongoing free lessons, this can be a good way to get started and assess if you want to continue with paid lessons.\n\nRemember, while free lessons can be a great starting point, investing in professional lessons can significantly enhance your singing skills in the long run. Always be cautious when engaging with strangers online and ensure you're using a safe and secure platform.",
